The paper deals with the problem of computing a maximal independent set in a multichannel radio network, which is a topic related to network protocols and distributed computing. Therefore, cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves graph theory and combinatorics, which suggests that it could be classified under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of logarithmic functions and polynomial bounds indicates that the paper may also be relevant to cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
